//help resources Enter altitude above the Earth surface in kilometers. Enter flight Mach number. This value uses to calculate flow full parameters. If this value equals zero only static parameters will be displayed. Static pressure in Pa. Density in kg/m^3. Static temperature in K. Full pressure of inlet flow in Pa. Full temperature of inlet flow in K. Sonic speed of the air in m/s. Enter altitude range in kilometers for parameters changing. Press OK button to generate graph. If no altitude was given program will work with default altitude range from 0 to 50 kilometers.
//menu resources Select mode Calculate Graph mode About
//About activity resources
This program intended to calculate atmosphere parameters on altitude from 0 to 85 kilometers above the Earth surface. Also it has possibility to evaluate full parameters of inlet flow during the flight with given altitude and Mach number.\n\n
